			<para
>There are good Unicode font lists on the net, as the one by Christoph Singer (<ulink url="http://www.slovo.info/unifonts.htm"
>Multilingual Unicode TrueType Fonts in the Internet</ulink
>), or the one by Alan Wood (<ulink url="http://www.alanwood.net/unicode/fontsbyrange.html"
> Unicode character ranges and the Unicode fonts that support them</ulink
>). </para>
			
		</sect3>
	</sect2>
	
	<sect2 id="hdbk-config-bt-profiles"
><title
><guimenu
>Display templates</guimenu
></title>
	
		<para
>Display templates define the rendering of text (colors, size etc.). Various built-in templates are available. If you select one, you will see a preview on the right pane.</para>
		
	</sect2>
	
	<sect2 id="hdbk-config-bt-profiles"
><title
><guimenu
>Sitzungen</guimenu
></title>
	
		<para
>Sessions define the appearance of the work area, for example which windows are open and which texts should be displayed in these windows. Once a session is created, you can use the menu item <menuchoice
><guimenu
>Window</guimenu
> <guimenuitem
>Save session</guimenuitem
></menuchoice
> to save the current session into an existing session file. Use <menuchoice
><guimenu
>Window</guimenu
><guimenuitem
>Load session </guimenuitem
></menuchoice
> to load a an existing session into &bibletime;. Play around with this helpful feature to see what you can do with it. For example, you might want to create one session with modules that you use for Bible study, and another one for devotional reading. Once you created and saved those sessions, you can switch between them quickly.</para>
		
	</sect2>

	<sect2 id="hdbk-config-bt-sword"
><title
><guimenu
>Sword</guimenu
></title>
	
		<para
>Many features provided by the Sword backend can now be customized in &bibletime;. These features are documented right in the dialog.</para>
		
	</sect2>
	
	<sect2 id="hdbk-config-bt-Accelerators"
><title
><guimenu
>HotKeys</guimenu
></title>
	
	<!-- TODO: RECREATE FONTCONFIG SCREENSHOT-->
	
		<para
>HotKeys are special key commands that can be used in the place of the menu items and icons. A number of &bibletime;'s commands have predefined HotKeys (see <link linkend="hdbk-reference-hotkeys"
>this section</link
> for a complete listing). All of &bibletime;'s commands can be assigned HotKeys here. This is very helpful to quickly access the functions that you need the most.</para>
	
	</sect2>

</sect1>
	
		
